cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper reports on a human subjects experiment to determine the salience of different types of symmetries in graphs. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper deals with the visualization of graphs and the perception of symmetries in them. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility as the paper discusses the perception of visual patterns (symmetries) in drawings. 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are less likely but still possible categories as they deal with perception and visualization, respectively.
